                <p class="text-justify">
                    The only floating water lake in the world. It is also the only fresh water lake in northeast india. There is a floating thick layers of grass called phumdis where people used to make houses and can stay.The Loktak Aquamarine Floating Homestay offers a unique option of accommodation on the Loktak Lake. After all, it’s not like every day that one gets to stay on a homestay that floats. Its location on one of the ‘Phumdis’ or small floating islands floats on the fresh water of Loktak Lake means that the homestay is floating. The fresh mild breeze swept above the water which makes so alive. Hence, staying a day in floating Aquamarine is an unforgettable experience of a lifetime. Besides, the best way to enjoy the magic of Loktak Lake is to stay in floating Aquamarine and enjoy the beauty of lake in Lotus blooming season.
